INSERT INTO public.apisourcedocuments (id, createdat, secondarykey, updatedat, apisource, description, ingestedat, lastcheck, lat, location, lon, text) VALUES (359923727978496, '2026-05-27 14:30:21.315031', NULL, NULL, 'placesGoogleApis', 'Restaurant, places of interes near of Desden, Deutschland', NULL, NULL, 51.0504088, 'Desden, Deutschland', 13.7372621, 'Near by places
The following is a list of restaurant, places of interes and others locals that are near of the location Desden, Deutschland.
Every entry contaion the following information:
- Place name
- Address
- Local type
- Phone number
- Website
- Reviews: a List rewiew made by people


Place name: Oskarshausen, Address: bei Dresden, Burgker Str. 39, 01705 Freital, Germany, Local type: amusement_park, go_karting_venue, indoor_playground, playground, race_course, amusement_center, sports_activity_location, event_venue, restaurant, point_of_interest, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 79992770 Website: http://www.oskarshausen.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: Fantastic day out, highly recommend for children and families - a lot to do.
Id say our 10 year old is really the upper age limit for the attractions.
The wristband is good value for money.
Lots to explore inside as well, although some of the activities can be a little more on the expensive side.
We found the food good value for money.
We also visited the pumpkin exhibition, also fantastic.
Looking forward to visiting in the Spring.. Review published on: 6 months ago

Rewiew: Variety of rides, slides, a small kids cinema. Also has lots of cafes.  The ticket and food prices are high though.
There are some hand crafting options for the kids at additional price.. Review published on: 7 months ago

Rewiew: You can enjoy without entrance fee. When you enter, you are asked to buy free pass for 12€. But most of the attraction needs additional fee and I don’t think free pass is needed. And it is better to bring cash because you use 1 or 2 €for attraction.. Review published on: 2 years ago

Place name: JOYNEXT Arena, Address: Magdeburger Str. 10, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: ice_skating_rink, bowling_alley, athletic_field, sports_complex, sports_activity_location, restaurant, point_of_interest, service, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 4885252 Website: http://www.dresden.de/eislaufen

Reviews


Rewiew: So fun in winter because you can skate both indoors and outdoors. Great if you have your own skates too but it’s only €5 per 2 hrs (as if 2026).. Review published on: 4 months ago

Rewiew: We went to our first ever hockey match in Germany last night and we had a fantastic time. It is a beautiful arena, we had great seats (comfortable for an ice rink!) and the staff was really helpful and friendly.
Plus: the amount of toilets and therefore fast turnover were almost mind blowing 😅
Temperatures were very comfortable, too. Jumper and softshell jacket were enough.
Prices at the bar were high but kinda normal for events.. Review published on: a year ago

Rewiew: OK 👍. Review published on: 2 months ago

Place name: McDonald''s, Address: Wilsdruffer Str. 19/21, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: fast_food_restaurant, restaurant, point_of_interest, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 4965087 Website: https://www.mcdonalds.com/de/de-de/restaurant-suche.html/l/dresden/wilsdruffer-strasse-19-21/449&cid=listing_0449

Reviews


Rewiew: We ordered our food and we wanted to go to the toilet but even if you are a McDonalds customer you have to pay 0.50 cents to be able to use the restroom. Food was okay like any other restaurant.. Review published on: 8 months ago

Rewiew: I visited in the morning, shorty after opening. The place was almost empty and the food was prepared fairly quickly. Coffee was great.
I haven''t visited the washroom, but I believe it''s paid washroom, as it is the case with all public washrooms in Germany.. Review published on: 12 months ago

Rewiew: Very big prices but food was good and tasty, you have to pay for toilet.. Review published on: 7 months ago

Place name: BallsportArena Dresden, Address: Weißeritzstr. 4, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: sports_complex, physiotherapist, athletic_field, sports_activity_location, health, event_venue, restaurant, point_of_interest, service, food, association_or_organization, establishment Phone number: 0351 4824940 Website: http://www.ballsportarena-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: I watched an amazing handball match Dresden against TUV and dresden won. Amazing drinks and foods and seats but you cant bring own drinks.. Review published on: 2 years ago

Rewiew: Perfect place for your indoor sports activities.. Review published on: 6 months ago

Rewiew: Great facility - use it regularly for some games of badminton - courts are good, the locker rooms are well maintained and the service is great!. Review published on: a year ago

Place name: Ristorante "Mamma Mia", Address: Kreuzstraße 1-3, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: italian_restaurant, family_restaurant, mediterranean_restaurant, noodle_shop, wine_bar, vegetarian_restaurant, european_restaurant, bar, restaurant, point_of_interest, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 4976600 Website: https://www.mammamia-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: Decent food and great service. Surprised that they charge €7 for water, which is more expensive than other drinks. The pasta I had was spicy, which I like, but quite salty. Nice selection of food and drinks. Good experience overall and would recommend coming here. It''s also easy to pay separately if you''re in a group.. Review published on: 8 months ago

Rewiew: Excellent pasta and sauces. Staff was quick and friendly. We will be coming back. It''s better to make a reservation but not necessarily id they have room for you.. Review published on: 4 months ago

Rewiew: very good quality handmade pasta, which tastes balanced and just perfect. also cozy atmosphere and warm, friendly service! definitely recommend. Review published on: 2 months ago

Place name: Radisson Blu Park Hotel & Conference Centre, Dresden Radebeul, Address: Nizzastraße 55, 01445 Radebeul, Germany, Local type: hotel, resort_hotel, bar, lodging, restaurant, point_of_interest, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 83210 Website: https://www.radissonhotels.com/en-us/hotels/radisson-blu-conference-dresden-radebeul?cid=a:se+b:gmb+c:emea+i:local+e:rdb+d:cese+h:DEDRSCCR

Reviews


Rewiew: This is a fairly big conference hotel. I didn''t stay here for a conference but it was still fine. A bit outside of the city so keep this in mind, I''d recommend having a car although there are public transport options as well. The bar is only open if there''s big conference ongoing. Breakfast and dinner were fine. Room was renovated - i''ve read the reviews about run down rooms in the other buildings but in the main building you don''t have to worry about this although you can still tell this is not the most modern hotel. Cleanliness okay-ish.

No reason to avoid this hotel but I will go back to an hotel in the Neustadt next time I come to Dresden.. Review published on: 3 months ago

Rewiew: Rooms are quite old, pillows are very uncomfortable and service is not good. They don’t clean your room if you don’t ask for it. We have paid for a breakfast however coffee was not good - (like a warm water only) and options were very limited. I don’t recommend this hotel as a four star hotel.. Review published on: 5 months ago

Rewiew: A hotel that smells very, very, very bad.
Of course, the bar, restaurant, and exterior are very impressive. But as soon as I opened the door to my room, everything changed... A musty smell, shabby walls, and dirt. Spiders live in every corner. Also, if you want to sleep with the windows open, be aware that at about 5:30 in the morning the irrigation system will turn on, which is very, very, very noisy (you can enjoy it in the attached video). But not only will the noise prevent you from getting a good night''s sleep - the pillows are of the worst quality I''ve ever seen (you can see in the photo), they are so thin that they look like a rug (but that''s why...).
I was also very impressed by the fact that a hotel of this class could not afford to include 1-2 bottles of plain water in the room price (this is the first time I''ve seen this). Even in the cheapest hotels, water is a must have! So, don''t bother buying it in a store, or at the hotel bar.
By the way, the bar is great!!!. Review published on: 9 months ago

Place name: Kutscherschänke, Address: Münzgasse 10, 01067 Dresden, Germany, Local type: german_restaurant, european_restaurant, restaurant, point_of_interest, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 4965123 Website: https://www.kutscherschaenke-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: What great authentic German food and vibe. I visited during December and the Christmas markets. It was very busy and many people left without getting in, but luckily I made a reservation in advance. The server was kind and fun and offered a great meal. And definitely get the apple strudel!. Review published on: 5 months ago

Rewiew: This place was amazing! Friendly atmosphere from the staff and the  food was great and affordable. Visiting first time from England but this place made us want to visit Dresden again 😃.. Review published on: 3 months ago

Rewiew: Good hearty food and a pleasant lady serving us. For an 11:30am early lunch we shared a goulash soup, and a Pork Schnitzel- both were very good, and the beers too!. Review published on: 8 months ago

Place name: Schwerelos - Das Achterbahnrestaurant, Address: Wr. Pl. 10, 01069 Dresden, Germany, Local type: german_restaurant, family_restaurant, tourist_attraction, european_restaurant, restaurant, point_of_interest, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 82127900 Website: https://rollercoaster-dresden.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: Super cool place to have a family branch. Friendly to the kids, there''s a cute kids playmat with toys here.
Food is being served through fun railways of different paths. Super cute Kitty robot brings drinks and takes away the dishes, can also sing you a "Happy birthday" song.🎂
Wanna say special thanks to our waiters Ulli and Ali.🤗🥰 We had lots of fun.😋
My daughter won a special Gift card for our next visit. We will definitely come back more than once.. Review published on: 3 months ago

Rewiew: It is not just a place with delicious food! It is also a whole exciting world full of surprises! We loved the service! At first we were greeted by a kind young man who explained the concept of the restaurant. Then a very sweet and kind waitress with very good English welcomed us and even offered to play a buzzer after the meal. Drinks are served by a sweet robot. By the way, if you wish, you can see how your dishes are being prepared through a peeking window, before they are sent to you via a whole huge rail system. Left us thinking how do the dishes know which table to go to?! The dishes were absolutely delicious! We were so hungry and so impressed with the food that we forgot to take photos... Slushy for grownups with a dash of tequila made the day even more fun! But we shall include it in our travel video vlog, to fully appreciate it!

Anyway, we would gladly come back anytime!. Review published on: 8 months ago

Rewiew: Awesome experience 🤖 I felt like I was teleported to Futurama universe. I believe this place would be the best option for a group gathering since the tables are big and watching the orders coming by is extremely fun. It is very close to the train station and prices are quite affordable. I feel lucky to experience such a unique place ✨. Review published on: a year ago

Place name: Campingplatz Dresden-Mockritz, Address: Boderitzer Str. 30, 01217 Dresden, Germany, Local type: campground, lodging, sports_activity_location, restaurant, point_of_interest, service, food, establishment Phone number: 0351 4715250 Website: https://www.cbm-camping.de/dresden/

Reviews


Rewiew: Nice and comfortable place. Showers were coin operated, however time and water pressure was great as well as privacy. Staff was super nice and very professional, good english. I can recommend this place for anyone visiting Dresden, you will not be disappointed.. Review published on: 9 months ago

Rewiew: Nice and professional staff, newly renovated, clean and well maintained bath- and service rooms. Bus access right outside the camping site, busses every 20 min. to beautiful Dresden. All in all a great site to stay over night or a few days.. Review published on: 10 months ago

Rewiew: Very nice and quiet camping, extraordinary service from owner Mandy. Very helpful and pleasant! Bus stop in front of camping with good connection to city center. I strongly recommend!
Warm greetings to Mandy!. Review published on: 8 months ago

Place name: Ballhaus Watzke, Address: Kötzschenbroder Str. 1, 01139 Dresden, Germany, Local type: brewpub, beer_garden, pub, banquet_hall, wedding_venue, bar, concert_hall, live_music_venue, auditorium, brewery, event_venue, restaurant, point_of_interest, service, food, manufacturer, establishment Phone number: 0351 852920 Website: http://www.watzke.de/

Reviews


Rewiew: The best (!) beer in Dresden (from the brewery Watzke) in their (out of the three) biggest and probably oldest brewery with a beer garden, views of the old town and great, traditional German food to go along with the beer. When in Dresden, this is a must!. Review published on: 6 months ago

Rewiew: We were here as park of our European beer tour guide, and if you don’t speak German, you may have some difficulty to order your beer and food, because the staffs here don’t speak English. Google translate becomes the helper.

The beer was very good. The food is very average at best! The sausage dish we ordered was not good at all!

Service was also very slow. But the atmosphere was nice.. Review published on: a year ago

Rewiew: perfect place to go during spring. lovely biergarten restaurant at dresden and you get perfect view of sunset by the river.  found my most favourite German cuisine steak au four!

all the beers are fresh and good.. Review published on: a year ago');
